<h1>Little Music Makers Course</h1>

<p>At 3 years of age children have a fascination with sound and music. In the Little Music Makers Course we use this fascination to explore a whole range of musical concepts in a fun and nurturing environment.</p>

<p>Children love these engaging music lessons which are designed to educate and foster a musical ear at this key developmental stage.</p>

<h2>Curriculum</h2>

<p>
	<strong>Rhythm</strong> – the beat of the music<br/>
	<strong>Pitch</strong> – how high or low a sound is<br/>
	<strong>Dynamics</strong> – loud and soft<br/>
	<strong>Tempo</strong> – the speed of the music<br/>
	<strong>Tone</strong> – the colour of the sound, what instrument is being played<br/>
	<strong>Texture</strong> – how different sounds combine together
</p>

<p>These concepts are discovered, explored and explained through fun activities such as singing, dancing, playing percussion instruments, keyboard playing and story telling.</p>

<p>As well as these key musical concepts, other important skills are nurtured and developed:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Learning further social skills including group cooperation and sharing</li>
	<li>Development of vocabulary and comprehension skills</li>
	<li>On-going confirmation of numeracy skills</li>
	<li>Development of coordination</li>
</ul>

<h2>Course Structure</h2>

<p>
	<strong>Lesson duration:</strong> 45 minutes per week during school terms<br/>
	<strong>Course duration:</strong> Four 10-week modules. The flexible structure of this course enables you to take between 1 to 4 modules, either sequentially or non-sequentially<br/>
	<strong>Class size:</strong> 4- 8 students
</p>


